{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774639905,"nonce":"qhoPssUxZqxAIiEuv6sudjdnV0g=","message":"## Cost correction: multi-model GPU packing\n\nThe original spec assumes 1 model per GPU, which dramatically overestimates cost. At batch=250, each model uses only **3.2% of GPU FLOPS** and **2.7 GB VRAM**. Running 4 models per GPU (as we currently do on RunPod) makes Modal cheaper than RunPod:\n\n| Scenario | GPUs | Wall-clock | Cost |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 8x L4, 1 model each, batch=250 | 8 | ~12 min | ~$1.28 |\n| 2x L4, 4 models each, batch=250 | 2 | ~12 min | ~$0.32 |\n| RunPod 2x4090, 4 models each | 2 | ~60-75 min | ~$0.85 |\n\n### Implementation\n\nThe `run_training` function should accept a `concurrency` parameter controlling how many training subprocesses to pack per GPU container. The `.map()` sweep logic would then bin conditions into chunks of `concurrency` and launch one container per chunk:\n\n```python\n@app.function(gpu=\"L4\", timeout=7200)\ndef run_training_batch(\n    script_path: str,\n    args_list: list[dict],  # multiple configs per container\n    run_ids: list[str],\n) -\u003e list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Run multiple training processes on a single GPU.\"\"\"\n    import subprocess, asyncio\n    procs = []\n    for args, rid in zip(args_list, run_ids):\n        cmd = build_command(script_path, args, rid)\n        procs.append(subprocess.Popen(cmd, ...))\n    # Wait for all, collect results\n    ...\n```\n\nThe sweep runner bins N conditions into ceil(N/concurrency) containers.\n\n### LR scaling as a future multiplier\n\nIf LR scaling with larger batch sizes validates (batch 20x bigger, LR 20x bigger, 20x fewer batches → same convergence), this changes the equation further: a single model at batch=5000 would use more of the GPU, potentially making 1-model-per-GPU efficient. This would simplify the wrapper (no subprocess packing) while also reducing total compute.\n\n**Action item**: Once LR scaling experiments complete, run a Modal benchmark comparing:\n1. 4 models/GPU at batch=250 (current approach, packed)\n2. 1 model/GPU at batch=5000 with scaled LR (simpler, potentially faster)\n3. 2 models/GPU at batch=2500 with scaled LR (hybrid)\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}